<div class="image-container floatright"><a href="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/fantem-s-poi-file/Fantem.png"><img src="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--resized-images/fantem-s-poi-file/Fantem.png/small.jpg" alt="Fantem.png" class="image" /></a></div>
<p><strong>POI name:</strong> <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/fantem" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1391641); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1391641&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869196" alt="Fantem" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1391641)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/fantem" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1391641); return false;">Fantem</a></span></p>
<p><strong>Gender:</strong> Female</p>
<p><strong>Serial Number:</strong> Ξ-BU66N7NY-1825</p>
<p><strong>Threat level:</strong> 2</p>
<p><strong>Site of Operations:</strong> Variable</p>
<p><strong>Profile:</strong> POI &quot;Fantem&quot; is an uncontained, anomalous entity resembling a 1.7&#160;m tall, humanoid variant of cryptid species 12-656 (&quot;wolpertinger&quot;). It is unknown whether Fantem is venomous or capable of flight, however it does possess appropriate limbs and teeth implying it is capable of both. Fantem is capable of level 2 reality bending or higher, having created or altered multiple items to possess anomalous properties, and appearing within Foundation's anomalous item storage facilities to recover multiple items linked to it.</p>
<p>Fantem possesses a humanoid body structure, overweight build, leporine ears and facial structure, a light brown fur coat, antlers resembling those of an adult female deer, large feathered wings, and sharp teeth. It was spotted after the discovery of a cabin near The B█████ Strid, which had contained multiple objects with varying anomalous properties.</p>
<p>Fantem has stolen the majority of objects with a link to it, however, this appears to be for sentimental reasons rather than for malicious intent (see Objects Associated).</p>
<p><strong>Objects Associated:</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>Item Description: A hooded lantern, estimated 1██ years old. Object does not require a fuel source to be lit, and can burn indefinitely.</p>
<p>Date of Recovery: ██-██-████<br />
Location of Recovery: The B█████ Strid, █████████<br />
Current Status: Stolen, currently expected to be possessed by POI 'Fantem'.</p>
<p><em>Notes: I still have use of this. I suppose I could make another, but I'd much rather have this one back. It was my first piece&#8230; Besides, it's not like you can't make your own.</em></p>
<p><em>~Fantem</em></p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>Item Description: A semi-animate hand-made doll resembling a young girl. Object is composed of cloth, leaves, and leather, and appears resilient to damage. Object seems to react to positive stimulus, ie: hugging back when hugged, and &quot;laughing&quot; during play.</p>
<p>Date of Recovery: ██-██-████<br />
Location of Recovery: The B█████ Strid, █████████<br />
Current Status: Stolen, currently expected to be possessed by POI 'Fantem'.</p>
<p><em>Notes: Thank you for getting this back&#8230; I know you didn't get it on my behalf, but&#8230; thanks.</em></p>
<p><em>~Fantem</em></p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>Item Description: A large book labeled &quot;The Fantem Family Story Book&quot;, estimated 1██ years old. When opened, object will spontaneously create a short story tailored for the reader or audience. All short stories appear to reference many mythologies, and focus on the drama and horror genres. If a subject has used the object before, and wishes to view a story previously viewed, it will receive that story upon opening instead of a new one. If a subject wants a specific mythology referenced in a new story, the object will create a story centering that mythology.</p>
<p>Date of Recovery: ██-██-████<br />
Location of Recovery: The B█████ Strid, █████████<br />
Current Status: Stolen, currently expected to be possessed by POI 'Fantem'.</p>
<p><em>Notes: I used to read this old thing. A lot.</em></p>
<p><em>~Fantem</em></p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>Item Description: a large herb planter. Object promotes rapid growth of any plant species planted inside it so it could be harvested within the next twenty-four hours.</p>
<p>Date of Recovery: ██-██-████<br />
Location of Recovery: The B█████ Strid, █████████<br />
Current Status: Site 45-C, floor 5, greenhouse #012. Currently used for growing yarrow (Achillea millefolium).</p>
<p><em>Notes: Keep it. Consider it payment for getting my stuff for me. I used to use it for medical supplies, but I don't really need it anymore. You could probably find more use for it than I could.</em></p>
<p><em>~Fantem</em></p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>Item Description: A child's coffin, housing the corpse of a young girl, estimated to be ten years old prior to death. When an object is placed inside the closed coffin, it preserves that object at the same state it was inserted. Surroundings suggest that the objects were buried approximately 100 years ago. The state the cadaver was found in suggests that she was placed within the coffin two hours after death. Cause of death: AD-NC-0-741 (&quot;Wood Heart&quot;) strain.</p>
<p>Date of Recovery: ██-██-████<br />
Location of Recovery: The B█████ Strid, █████████<br />
Current Status:</p>
<ul>
<li>Coffin: Site 45-C, floor 12.</li>
<li>Cadaver: Site 45-C, floor 5, greenhouse #008</li>
</ul>
<p><em>Notes: &#8230; I was trying to prevent this&#8230; She left behind something beautiful though, didn't she?&#8230; Keep her. She'll be safe here.</em></p>
<p><em>~Fantem</em></p>
</blockquote>
